node.text:
We're kicking off our first est film production with a momentous Malvern Home renovation by @dohertydesignstudio from est magazine issue #35.
.
Tapping into its rich architectural past and 1980s new wave bones, @dohertydesignstudio have skilfully commandeered an epic journey to reinvent this Melbourne family home. An original 1980's design by architect Peter McIntyre. .
.
Experience the entire home via the link in profile or read the full feature in est magazine issue #35. .
.
Design @dohertydesignstudio
Building design @arialexander
Builder @north_building_group 
Styling @heathernetteking 
Florals and assitant styling @rachelpolivkastylist 
Art consultant @gb.art.consulting 
Landscape design @benscott_design 
Videography @richardlipp.studio
Words @meganmayrawson
Art @tompolo @liamsnootle @anyapesce @oocaleb @davidjamesgriggs @christianthompsonartist #leekyoung-hwa 
Furniture & Objects @domoaustralia @lightlydesign @loomtowels @fenton_and_fenton @abode_living @moderntimesau @ajarfurniture @lamarzoccohomeau

node.text:
Great land. Great architecture. Great living. In an est exclusive, we feature three unique films by Rob Mills Architecture & Interiors (RMA). Australian-based RMA’s latest project, a ground-breaking residence in Byron Bay incorporates Mill’s signature use of drama, curves, lines, light and a reflection of the qualities of the land.
.
View all three films via link in profile.
.
Videography @collider__
Creative Direction | Design @robmillsarchitects

node.text:
ARCHITECTURE | Xerolithi House
​.
​@sinas_architects' Xerolithi House takes its name from the stone retaining walls 
​that shape the project, immersing it in the rugged landscape.
​.
The stone walls create protected outdoor pockets and areas to enjoy the Aegean sea views – like this alfresco dining space. 
​.
​Design @sinas_architects in collaboration with @mamouramaria @olgaktena 
​Photography @yiorgoskordakis
​Styling @anestismichalis 

​https://estliving.com/

node.text:
HOME TOUR | Brussels Apartment
​.
​“We owe the planet a conscious approach about the use and reuse of materials – if we can restore a noble and beautiful material we will always try to do so.”
– Architect Stef Claes
​.
Belgian architect @stef_claes breathes a sense of life and longevity into his most recent project, the redesign of an inner-city Brussels apartment.
​.
​Read more about Stef's approach to the Brussels Apartment on est – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @stef_claes
​Art and styling  Michael Vertessen
​Photography @cb
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/brussels-apartment-stef-claes/

node.text:
WEDNESDAY WINE & DINE | The Beach House
​.
​@studioesteta granted one of Geelong's most memorable Art Deco buildings a new lease of life in their latest hospitality project, The Beach House.
​.
Located within the iconic, heritage-listed Eastern Beach Bathers pavilion in Geelong, Victoria, @studioesteta have reimagined the quintessential Australian beachside kiosk through materials that reflect the sun and sand.
.
The new space offers a relaxed cafe setting with beach views by day and a dining and cocktail experience by night. 
​.
Design @studioesteta
​Photography @seanfennessy
​.
https://www.estliving.com

node.text:
DESIGN | Bringing Sustainability to the Fore in the Bathroom
​.
@fantini_official, @falperdesign and @ceramicacatalano are all recognisable names in the bathroom, known for their superior Italian craftsmanship and classic design aesthetic. 
​.
​At the same time, they are defined by their environmentally conscious efforts to design bathroom products that are better for people and the planet. 
​
Together with @rogerseller, ​we spotlight these three brands on how they’re actively paving the way for a more sustainable future. 
​.
​Read more on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Featuring projects by;
​Design @kestielanestudio, @sandersandking, @studioprineas, @larrittevans, @vincentvanduysen and @carr_au
​Photography @peterclarkephoto, @evegwilson, @sharyncairns, @davekulesza & @chriswarnes 
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/sustainable-bathroom-design/

node.text:
DESIGNER FOCUS | Happy Birthday Pierre Yovanovitch!
​
In the spirit of French interior architect @pierre.yovanovitch's birthday, we're revisiting his own home which he shared with us in est Magazine Issue #37  - Chateau Fabregues, set in the lavender foothills of the high alps in Provence, France. 
​.
​Pierre says Chateau Fabregues is his heart and soul and lifelong project. “It’s a blank canvas for me where I’m able to express myself creatively and also a place for me ground myself surrounded in nature and with my family – four-legged members included.” 
​.
Explore Pierre Yovanovitch's countryside home in full on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @pierre.yovanovitch 
​Photography @guillaumedelaubier, @jeanfrancoisjaussaud, @jeromegalland & @matthieusalvaing
​.
https://www.estliving.com/at-home-with-pierre-yovanovitch/

HOME TOUR | Kortrijk House
​
​Near the French border in the Flemish province of West Flanders, Belgium lies the city of Kortrijk. 
​.
​For a project of the same name, @govaertvanhoutte and @atelier10.8 have transformed a former barn into a warm and tactile family home by introducing a subdued material palette that pays tribute to the building’s heritage.

​.
​As a complete reimagining, Alma House sees the remodelling of an existing building from the inside out. 
​.
​Taking cues from the site’s storied past and creating new connections internally, @atelierbarda carve out a subdued home that feels far removed – and readily connected – at once to its Montreal setting.
​.
​Read more about the Alma House on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @atelierbarda 
​Photography @alexlesage__
​Words @bronwynmarshall 
​.

Landaraburu Borda, designed by Spanish architect @jordihidalgo_arquitectura, comprises of a rural home and concrete annex carved into the hillside, connected through a glass corridor.

The project expresses a deep respect for its location in the Navarre mountains and the old existing stone building on site. 
​.
​Design @jordihidalgo_arquitectura
​Photography #joséhevia
​.

node.text:
AT HOME WITH | Chan & Eayrs
​.
@chanandeayrs converted this loft space in London's Shoreditch by favouring tactility and custom details – from the natural oak kitchen joinery to the linen shutters above the bath. 
​.
Standout pieces in their home include the iconic Camaleonda sofa, designed in 1970 by Mario Bellini and The Water Monopoly Rockwell bath that reflects the serene mint green thread throughout. 
​.
​Design @chanandeayrs
​Photography @_martin_morrell
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/
